title: SpaceX plans Starlink and Polaris Dawn launches in consecutive days
summary: SpaceX is planning to launch a Starlink flight on Thursday and its groundbreaking Polaris Dawn mission on Friday, marking two significant launches...

title: Poor recovery weather causes SpaceX to scrub the launch of 21 Starlink satellites from Cape Canaveral
summary: The launch from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station was delayed a day due to poor weather in the booster landing zone. Liftoff is set for Thursday, Sept. 5, at 8:35 a.m. EDT (1235 UTC).
